y more chaotic evolution than in collisionless simulations, making\nit much harder to identify individual progenitors using phase space coordinates\nalone. However by combining information on stellar ages and chemical abundances\nwith the orbital properties of halo stars in the underlying self-consistent\npotential, the identification of progenitors is likely to be possible.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 18 Jan 2013 22:51:26 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 28 Feb 2013 22:43:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
